text: Zeeshan Malik (born 26 December 1996) is a Pakistani cricketer. He made his Twenty20 debut on 8 September 2016 for Rawalpindi in the 2016–17 National T20 Cup. Prior to his T20 debut, he was part of Pakistan's squad for the 2016 Under-19 Cricket World Cup. He made his first-class debut for Rawalpindi in the 2016–17 Quaid-e-Azam Trophy on 1 October 2016. In December 2018, he was named in Pakistan's team for the 2018 ACC Emerging Teams Asia Cup. In March 2019, he was named in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa's squad for the 2019 Pakistan Cup. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Pakistani cricketers Category:Rawalpindi cricketers Category:People from Chakwal District
